            <p>A security control framework is a collection of techniques and processes to help you manage a range of security risks.</p>

            <h2 id="reflect-your-context-and-risk-appetite">Choose a framework</h2>

            <p>Use a framework that fits your project best. You might need to explain why you have chosen a particular framework.</p>

            <p>The Defence Secure by Design approach is based on the cyber security framework from the National Institute of Standards and Technology (NIST), U.S. Department of Commerce.</p>

            <p>Find out <a href="https://www.nist.gov/cyberframework" target="_blank">more about the NIST framework<span class="govuk-visually-hidden"> (opens in a new tab)</span></a>.</p>

            <p>You can <a href="https://www.security.gov.uk/guidance/secure-by-design/activities/agreeing-a-security-controls-set-for-your-service" target="_blank">other frameworks listed on GOV.UK<span class="govuk-visually-hidden"> (opens in a new tab)</span></a>.</p>


            <h2 id="map-controls-against-risks">Map controls against risks</h2>

            <p>Whatever framework you follow, run a team workshop to agree the controls you will use.</p>

            <p>You need to:</p>

            <ul>
              <li>describe why the controls are right for your technology or service</li>
              <li>firewalls</li>
              <li>list your controls and the risks they will manage</li>
              <li>create [high level control documentation] that the team can access and your stakeholders can understand</li>
            </ul>

            <p>You can <a href="" target="_blank">check what to include in your list of controls<span class="govuk-visually-hidden"> (opens in a new tab)</span></a>.</p>

            <h2 id="put-your-controls-in-place">Put your controls in place</h2>

            <p>After agreeing your controls, your team is responsible for setting up and monitoring them. Your Senior Responsible Owner (SRO) is accountable for controls being in place and working.</p>
            
